-- Czech Stocks: Kit Digital, Erste Group Bank Are Active in Prague
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-03-30T14:45:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-30/czech-stocks-kit-digital-erste-group-bank-are-active-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
rose 0.4 percent to 973.1 at the close in  Prague , paring weekly
losses to 1.5 percent and ending the quarter up 6.8 percent.  The following were among the most active  equities  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   of Austria rose 1.4 percent
to 427 koruna, reducing weekly losses to 6 percent. The stock
gained 24 percent this quarter, the most since the third quarter
of 2009.  Global shares extended the best first-quarter rally since
1998 and the euro gained as European finance ministers agreed to
increase rescue fund and a U.S. report showed personal spending
in the world’s largest economy grew more than forecast.  Kit Digital Inc. (KITD)   jumped 17 percent, the most in
almost five months, to 141 koruna after  Roth Capital Partners 
said yesterday the maker of online video software may put itself
up for sale.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
